text: The canton of Meaux is an administrative division of the Seine-et-Marne department, in northern France. It was created at the French canton reorganisation which came into effect in March 2015. Its seat is in Meaux.Décret n° 2014-186 du 18 février 2014 portant délimitation des cantons dans le département de Seine-et-Marne It consists of the commune of Meaux. ==References== Category:Cantons of Seine-et-Marne
